messages.message:
Hi,

has anyone seen this mypy error before in the python unit tests.

```/pyenv/versions/3.7.3/lib/python3.7/site-packages/werkzeug/serving.py:224: error: misplaced type annotation```
Quick google search tells me that `misplaced type annotation` generally occurs if type annotation is present after opening brackets like:

```// src: https://github.com/pallets/werkzeug/blob/30c7336136e16365ca2f42deb78f778eebfc772f/src/werkzeug/serving.py#L224

peer_cert = self.connection.getpeercert(  # type: ignore[attr-defined]
                binary_form=True
            )```
How would you handle this for a third party python package? any pointers to debug this?
